  "text": "Tcr loci recombine in developing T but not developing B cells while the reciprocal is true for recombination of Ig loci, with the exception that Igh D-to-J recombination can be detected in thymocytes [CITATION_1] . We find that RAG binding exhibits a similar lineage specificity: RAG1 and RAG2 do not bind detectably to Db, Jb, or Ja gene segments in WT pre-B cells, or to Vk or Jk gene segments in WT pre-T cells, while there appears to be a low level of binding in the vicinity of Jh1 in pre-T cells ( Figures S3D and S3E ).",
